snippet.textDisplay: Maybe City will be a different prospect come the knock-out phase of the Champions League, but if they're still playing the way they are, I think that competition lends itself even less to City's style than the Premier league is doing right now. Everyone who's beaten City this season has done it by being brave and leaving people up top and having a go at them. The people who try to sit tight and ride it out are the ones who get snotted. Trouble is, in knock-out football, there's no room for sitting tight, you have to go for it in every game. So City are going to have some pretty good teams having a right go at them in every game of the knock-out stage of CL, and they're not coping at all well with that.

Leicester has no European games, so much less matches, no Club World Championships etc. But the winter is here, it´s long and it´s dark, night is full of horrors for Leicester as well. Couple key player injuries, and they´d struggle. However I believe, Leicester will be within top 4, ManCity will man up to be 2nd or 3rd, and the 4th UCL place is for almost anyone to take: Chelsea, Tottenham, Wolves, (Arsenal if they get Benitez).
edit. ManU NOT a threat at the moment, sorry.
